node.text: These past few weeks have been HELL! I want you guys all to be aware and careful! A few weeks ago, I got into a car accident because I fainted at the wheel. I was hospitalized and all my tests came back ok. However I found out I was covid positive. I had no clue and had no symptoms besides feeling a little tired and weak, which is normal to me since I workout everyday. A week later I had much worse symptoms and was out of it for almost two weeks. I am feeling better now but It was a nightmare and something I wouldn’t want anyone to go through with their family. My point is please BE CAREFUL! I know it seems as though covid has diminished and things are getting back to normal but it is still very much in circulation. Don’t take it lightly and if you are going out, just take proper precautions. 🙏🏼
